skill-development-description:
My most experience is in web development, especially back-end. When I do personal development, I often do the front end (react) as well, so I should be able to do that to some extent (I have no problem writing logic, but I can't design at all, so I tend to use templates). 
I have never touched the Ôºån embedded system at all, and I am interested in touching the parts close to the hardware, but I have not been able to touch it yet because I do not have enough knowledge of electric and logic circuits. 
I also have no experience with Java, and have only touched Java at the level of a university lecture, and have not been able to do it because it is difficult to do it on my own. 
I am currently involved in the development of ﬂãn applications (especially native application development), but I can't say that I have much development experience since I have basically only touched the api server side. I would like to learn how to use rust (tauri) for desktop development in the future.
skill-infrastructure-description:
I have only studied a little about infrastructure for development. However, I use Linux (ubuntu) as my main OS and have built several servers locally without using dokcer, so I have a little knowledge of servers. I have learned about networking and security several times through books and videos, but I have not been able to do much practical work. As for databases, I have some knowledge and experience in table design and SQL and beyond, but I have not studied indexing and normalization from scratch in reference books, so I would like to learn from scratch when I have time. I have also learned about the 
 cloud, but in fact, due to financial problems, I have not been able to get my hands on it as an individual. However, I plan to publish this site on AWS, and I would like to actively use relatively inexpensive services such as S3 in the future.
skill-others-description: There are many areas that I have not been able to get a handle on outside of development and infrastructure, and I have very little knowledge of test code, design, or development methodology. I am very interested in learning test code, which I aim to learn concurrently with learning RUST, and design. I have no communication skills at all, so I will be working on this and English, which I have barely studied since high school. Recently, I have been given a great opportunity to attend meetings with the front desk staff of another company, so my goal is to improve my ability to explain things in a concise manner. In addition to that, I would like to attend various conferences and other opportunities to connect with others (if you have any recommendations, I would love to hear them üôè ). I have a vague knowledge of software design, but no definite knowledge. I feel like I spend the most time on anything, whether it's table design or application design (I worry too much)...
